A sermon preached in the cathedrall church of York before Hi[s] Excellence the Earle of Newcastle and many of the prime nobility and gentry of the northerne covnties : at the publick thanksgiving to Almighty God for the late great victory upon Fryday, June 30, 1643, and the reducement of the west parts of Yorkeshire to obedience. Bramhall, John, 1594-1663.
[6], 26 p.
By Stephen Bulkley, Printed at York : 1643.
Attributed by Wing and NUC pre-1956 imprints to Bramhall. Dedication signed: Joh. Derensis [i.e. John Bramhall] Page 25 misnumbered 16. Reproduction of original in the British Library.
